  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under<strong> cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is starting to boil, preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving – this is your <strong>sticky rice</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half lengthways, then wash to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Cut the <strong>halved leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into rough bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut 1 piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>chopped leeks</strong> in the middle of the <strong>tin foil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the <strong>tin foil</strong> together around the leeks to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until the leeks have softened – these are your <strong>slow-roast leeks</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>wasabi paste</strong> (save the rest for later!) and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>wasabi mixture</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice the<strong> spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p><p>Pat the<strong> rump steaks</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong>, drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2141Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
